      • isLocalOnly

        public boolean isLocalOnly​()
        Checks whether PasteData is set for local access only. If this has not been set before, PasteData in the distributed pasteboard can be shared between devices by default.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the PasteData is set to Local Only; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • setLocalOnly

        public void setLocalOnly​(boolean isLocalOnly)
        Sets PasteData for local access only.

        In the distributed pasteboard scenario, if the passed argument is true, the PasteData will not be written across devices.

        Parameters:
        isLocalOnly - Specifies whether the PasteData is set to Local Only. true indicates the PasteData is accessed locally and cannot be shared among device, and indicates that the PasteData is shared among devices.
        Since:
        1
